1:25 p.m.  Defendant present in court without counsel.  Andrew Christenson for the State of Wisconsin.  Statement by defendant - has met with the DA.  DA recites plea agreement, upon plea to the charge, will recommend a fine and costs and will dismiss the repeater and place enhancer.  Defendant concurs.  Court goes over right to counsel.  Defendant waives right to counsel.  Court accepts waiver.  Defendant will enter a plea of NO CONTEST.  Court goes over constitutional rights with the defendant - defendant waives these rights.  Court goes over the elements of each offense.  Court instructs defendant of the maximum penalty.  Court instructs defendant regarding deportation.  Defendant enters a plea of NO CONTEST.  

Court finds the plea is made freely, voluntarily, intelligently and understandingly.  Court finds there is a factual basis to support the plea.  Court finds the defendant guilty to count 1.  Court strikes the repeater and place enhancer.  Court orders the judgment of conviction be entered here today.  Sentencing statement by DA.  Statement by the defendant.

Court sentences the defendant to:  $250 fine plus costs.  Court grants the defendant 60 days to pay or payment plan.
